- create static shaders for experimentation here and later see if swe need something
more dynamic

Compilation Command

slangc -lang slang -matrix-layout-column-major -restrictive-capability-check -target spirv -std 2018 --

To enable some extension slang compiler exposes capabilities

slangc -lang slang -matrix-layout-column-major -restrictive-capability-check -capability spvVulkanMemoryModelKHR -target spirv -std 2018 -o .\triangle.vert.slang.spv -- .\triangle.vert.slang

Example to compile multiple shader stages from a single file, specifying a shader model (which slangc calls "profile")

```
slangc -profile glsl_450 -entry fragmentEntry -matrix-layout-column-major -restrictive-capability-check -capability spvVulkanMemoryModelKHR -stage fragment -target spirv -std 2018 -o .\basic-triangle.frag.spv -- .\basic-triangle.slang
slangc -profile glsl_450 -entry vertexEntry -matrix-layout-column-major -restrictive-capability-check -capability spvVulkanMemoryModelKHR -stage vertex -target spirv -std 2018 -o .\basic-triangle.vert.spv -- .\basic-triangle.slang
```
Warning: By default, even if you define an arbitrary name for a shader entry point so that slang doesn't give you an
error when packing multiple entry points together, the resulting SPIR-V binaries still use "main" as `OpEntryPoint`

```
PS Y:\Aether-Vk\shaders> spirv-dis .\basic-triangle.vert.spv
; SPIR-V
; Version: 1.3
; Generator: Khronos Slang Compiler; 0
; Bound: 35
; Schema: 0
               OpCapability Shader
               OpCapability VulkanMemoryModel
               OpExtension "SPV_KHR_vulkan_memory_model"
               OpMemoryModel Logical Vulkan
               OpEntryPoint Vertex %vertexEntry "main" %gl_Position %entryPointParam_vertexEntry_Color %input_Position %input_Color
               OpSource Slang 1
               OpName %input_Position "input.Position"
               OpName %input_Color "input.Color"
               OpName %entryPointParam_vertexEntry_Color "entryPointParam_vertexEntry.Color"
               OpName %vertexEntry "vertexEntry"
               OpDecorate %input_Position Location 0
               OpDecorate %input_Color Location 1
               OpDecorate %gl_Position BuiltIn Position
               OpDecorate %entryPointParam_vertexEntry_Color Location 0
       %void = OpTypeVoid
          %3 = OpTypeFunction %void
      %float = OpTypeFloat 32
    %v4float = OpTypeVector %float 4
    %v3float = OpTypeVector %float 3
%_ptr_Input_v3float = OpTypePointer Input %v3float
    %float_1 = OpConstant %float 1
%_ptr_Output_v4float = OpTypePointer Output %v4float
%_ptr_Output_v3float = OpTypePointer Output %v3float
%input_Position = OpVariable %_ptr_Input_v3float Input
%input_Color = OpVariable %_ptr_Input_v3float Input
%gl_Position = OpVariable %_ptr_Output_v4float Output
%entryPointParam_vertexEntry_Color = OpVariable %_ptr_Output_v3float Output
%vertexEntry = OpFunction %void None %3
          %4 = OpLabel
         %11 = OpLoad %v3float %input_Position
         %14 = OpLoad %v3float %input_Color
         %20 = OpCompositeConstruct %v4float %11 %float_1
               OpStore %gl_Position %20
               OpStore %entryPointParam_vertexEntry_Color %14
               OpReturn
               OpFunctionEnd
```
